Astarta Holding NV (AST) , a Ukrainian
agriculture company and a sugar maker, obtained a $60 million
loan from the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development
to expand its dairy business and to increase its land.  The company will also purchase agriculture machinery and
upgrade its sugar industry, the London-based bank said today in
an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
